channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: CNN Interview With Rapper Cam'ron About Diddy Goes Sideways in Jaw-Dropping Way
Trump campaign says it will sue 'The Apprentice' filmmakers: 'This garbage is pure fiction'
item.description: Former President Trump's team intends to file a lawsuit against the filmmakers behind "The Apprentice," a movie about Trump's life in the 1980s that the campaign calls "pure fiction."

item.title: Napolitano to Newsmax: Mistake to Have Put Any Defense Witnesses on Stand
item.description: It was a mistake by the defense in former President Donald Trump's New York business documents case to put any witness on the stand, former New Jersey Superior Court Judge Andrew Napolitano told Newsmax on Tuesday.

item.title: Ultra Right Beer Unveils Anti-Woke Bro Dude New Ad: 'How's That for Tone?'
Trump says he 'will never advocate imposing restrictions on birth control' or other contraceptives
item.description: Former President Trump said "will never advocate imposing restrictions on birth control," and vowed to ensure the Republican Party would not support a ban on any contraceptives.

item.title: Senators: Investigate Formula 1 on Andretti Denial
item.description: A group of senators are asking the Justice Department and the Federal Trade Commission to investigate Formula One after it rejected Michael Andretti's application to join the group with a new team, The Hill reported.

item.title: Rashida Tlaib Funneled Hundreds of Thousands of Dollars to Anti-Israel Activist Tied to Terrorist Groups
Top Trump allies meet with Netanyahu in Israel as ICC seeks arrest warrants
item.description: A delegation of Trump allies traveled to Israel to meet with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and his top political rival this week.

item.title: Mark Esper: 'Cool War Brewing With China' and US
item.description: Former Defense Secretary Mark Esper this week warned of a "cool war brewing with China" due to increasing economic and political competition with the United States.

item.title: Vacation Season Cautions: Large Animals Can Be Dangerous
Key Trump witness nixed after Merchan's stringent rulings reveals what his testimony would have been
item.description: Former FEC Commissioner Bradley Smith was set to testify in NY v. Trump, but was not brought before the court after presiding judge curbed what he could discuss.

item.title: Giuliani Pleads Not Guilty in Arizona Election Case
item.description: Former New York City Mayor Rudy Giuliani pleaded not guilty Tuesday to nine felony charges stemming from his alleged role in an effort to overturn Donald Trump's 2020 election loss in Arizona to Joe Biden.

item.title: CNN Analyst Elie Honig Eviscerates Bragg Prosecution and Michael Cohen for His Stunning Admission
Anti-Israel agitators interrupt Blinken Senate testimony, hauled out by Capitol police
item.description: Anti-Israel protesters interrupting a Senate hearing with Secretary of State Antony Blinken were shouting that Blinken is a "war criminal" guilty of "genocide."

item.title: Karoline Leavitt to Newsmax: 'Prosecution Has Not Proven a Crime' in N.Y. Trump Case
item.description: The prosecution in Donald Trump's legal expenses trial "has not proven a crime," but Judge Juan Merchan is going to force the trial to the jury, Trump campaign national press secretary Karoline Leavitt told Newsmax.
